Nigeria is said to be attracting more foreign direct investment in the pharmaceutical sub-sector owing to her population size, emerging market economy, to mention just a few. Making this submission recently in Lagos was the Country Representative of Hi Geen in Nigeria, Mr Amro Alabsi. Alabsi, who spoke at the launch of Hi Green, said the company decided to come to Nigeria as it sees the country as a good place to invest. Upbeat, Alabsi said, “We see Nigeria as a very good market and we feel Nigerians deserve the best products. Of course, Nigeria has all the attractive elements for investment, the most important of which are security, infrastructure, and educated and hardworking population. They are very energetic, creative and have entrepreneur spirit.”   Winner gets car in Bigi’s ‘Watch & Win’ promo     Firm unveils Camelot Mews in Lekki     FHA Mortgage Bank earns DataPro’s “BBB” rating   On the brand’s partnership with Imperial Madeiz, the brand representative in Nigeria, he said, “Dr Kofi Samir reached out to us and we sent samples of our products which were well received by patients who used them. We decided to partner with Imperial Madeiz because he understands the business and the products; we have confidence in his ability to push these products into the Nigerian market and make a success of it.” Also speaking, Dr Kofi Samir, Managing Director, Imperial Madeiz noted that the Hi Geen products had a quality others in the market don’t have. He added that the products were lifesavers for Nigerians who need those kinds of products. “The products are made from natural ingredients especially herbs and oils, so safe to use. They have everything including orthopedics and health care, nursing, personal care products, skin care, sanitisers and much more. “The products are of the highest quality which I can vouch for as a doctor with thirty years experience. So, our customers will get value for their money.”